#MEM id=traction-eos source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/SKILL.md savings=0%
M||tx|---
M||name|traction-eos
M||desc|'im the Entrepreneurial Operating sy (EOS) to align vision and execution across a company. Use when the us mentions "EOS", "V/TO", "quarterly rocks", "Level 10 meetings", "accountability chart", "IDS process", "Entrepreneurial Operating sy", or "business operating sy". Also trigger when a growing company needs meeting structure, goal-setting frameworks, or a systematic approach to solving recurring organizational issues. Covers the six EOS cp: Vision, People, Data, Issues, Process, Traction. For team motivation ds, see drive-motivation. For lean experimentation, see lean-startup.'
M||lice|MIT
M||meta|
M||auth|wondelai
M||vers|"1.1.0"
M||tx|---
M|Entr|tx|A complete sy for running a business w/ six key cp. Designed for entrepreneurial companies ($2M-$50M rv, 10-250 employees) that want to align vision and execution.
M|Core|**Mo|people, vision, traction.** EOS provides a simple, complete operating sy that strengthens the Six Key cp of any organization.
M|Core|**Th|** Great vision w/o traction is hallucination. Traction w/o vision is aimless. EOS connects the two through a practical, weekly operating rhythm.
M|Scor|**Go|10/10.** When evaluating or implementing business processes, rate 0-10 based on EOS cp strength. A 10/10 means all six cp are strong, meetings are productive, and quarterly rocks are consistently achieved; lower scores indicate gaps. Always provide current score and improvements to reach 10/10.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Vision → People → Data → Issues → Process → Traction
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Every business is built on these six cp. EOS strengthens all six.
M|1. V|**Qu|** Does everyone in the organization know where you're going and how you plan to get there?
M|1. V|**To|Vision/Traction Organizer (V/TO)**
M|1. V|The |
M|1. V|tx|\| Question \| What It Defines \| Example \|
M|1. V|tx|\|----------\|----------------\|---------\|
M|1. V|tx|\| **Core Values** \| 3-7 non-negotiable beliefs \| "Own it", "Do the right thing", "Grow or die" \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **Core Focus** \| Purpose/cause/passion + niche \| "Simplify small business" + "Cloud accounting" \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **10-Year Target** \| Big, hairy, audacious goal \| "$100M rv" or "10,000 cs" \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **mk st** \| Target mk, 3 uniques, proven process, guarantee \| Who you serve, why you're different \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **3-Year Picture** \| What company looks like in 3 years \| rv, profit, headcount, key metrics \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **1-Year Plan** \| rv, profit, measurables, goals \| Specific targets for this year \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **Quarterly Rocks** \| 3-7 priorities for this quarter \| The most important things to accomplish in 90 days \|
M|1. V|tx|\| **Issues List** \| All unresolved obstacles \| Problems, ideas, opportunities to discuss \|
M|1. V|**Pr|**
M|1. V|tx|1. Leadership team completes V/TO together (2-day off-site)
M|1. V|tx|2. Share w/ entire organization
M|1. V|tx|3. rv quarterly
M|1. V|tx|4. up annually
M|1. V|**Ke|** If leadership team can't agree on V/TO, you have a bigger problem. Alignment comes first.
M|1. V|See|[references/vto.md](references/vto.md) for V/TO templates and exercises.
M|2. P|**Qu|** Do you have the right people in the right seats?
M|2. P|**To|Accountability Chart**
M|2. P|tx|Not an org chart—an accountability chart. Defines the structure and who owns what.
M|2. P|**St|**
M|2. P|tx|```
M|2. P|tx|Visionary ←→ Integrator
M|2. P|tx|├── Sales/mk
M|2. P|tx|├── Operations
M|2. P|tx|└── fi
M|2. P|tx|```
M|2. P|**Tw|**
M|2. P|- **|** Big ideas, culture, key relationships, creative problem solving
M|2. P|- **|** Runs business day-to-day, manages team, executes vision, resolves conflicts
M|2. P|**Ru|** One person per seat. No shared accountability.
M|2. P|**To|People Analyzer**
M|2. P|Eval|
M|2. P|tx|**1. Right Person (core values fit)**
M|2. P|tx|\| Core Value \| + (most of the time) \| +/- (sometimes) \| - (rarely) \|
M|2. P|tx|\|-----------\|---------------------\|-----------------\|------------\|
M|2. P|tx|\| Own it \| + \| \| \|
M|2. P|tx|\| Do the right thing \| \| +/- \| \|
M|2. P|tx|\| Grow or die \| + \| \| \|
M|2. P|**St|** Must be "+" on all core values. One "+/-" is a conversation. Any "-" is wrong person.
M|2. P|tx|**2. Right Seat (GWC)**
M|2. P|- **|Understands the role
M|2. P|- **|Genuinely wants the role
M|2. P|- **|Has the mental, physical, emotional capacity
M|2. P|tx|**Must be "yes" on all three.** If missing any one, wrong seat.
M|2. P|**Th|** Right People + Right Seats = A-players
M|2. P|**Pe|**
M|2. P|it|Right person, right seat → Keep and invest in
M|2. P|it|Right person, wrong seat → Move to right seat
M|2. P|it|Wrong person, right seat → Coaching/exit (hardest call)
M|2. P|it|Wrong person, wrong seat → Exit immediately
M|2. P|See|[references/people.md](references/people.md) for accountability chart and people analyzer templates.
M|3. D|**Qu|** Are you managing based on objective data, or subjective opinions?
M|3. D|**To|Scorecard**
M|3. D|tx|A weekly rp card of 5-15 numbers that tell you how the business is doing.
M|3. D|**Sc|**
M|3. D|it|Activity-based metrics (leading indicators), not results (lagging)
M|3. D|it|Weekly numbers (monthly is too slow)
M|3. D|it|Every number has an owner
M|3. D|it|Every number has a goal
M|3. D|- Re|on track or off track
M|3. D|**Ex|**
M|3. D|tx|\| Metric \| Owner \| Goal \| W1 \| W2 \| W3 \| W4 \|
M|3. D|tx|\|--------\|-------\|------\|----\|----\|----\|----\|
M|3. D|tx|\| rv \| Sales Lead \| $50K/wk \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✗ \| ✓ \|
M|3. D|tx|\| New Leads \| mk \| 100/wk \| ✓ \| ✗ \| ✓ \| ✓ \|
M|3. D|tx|\| Demos done \| Sales \| 20/wk \| ✗ \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ \|
M|3. D|tx|\| cs NPS \| Support \| >50 \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ \|
M|3. D|tx|\| Cash Balance \| fi \| >$200K \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ \| ✓ \|
M|3. D|**Be|**
M|3. D|it|Spot problems 2-4 weeks earlier
M|3. D|it|Reduce "gut feeling" management
M|3. D|it|cr accountability w/o micromanagement
M|3. D|it|Everyone knows the score
M|3. D|**Me|** If you had to go on vacation for 4 weeks, what 5-15 numbers wld tell you how the business is doing?
M|3. D|See|[references/data.md](references/data.md) for scorecard templates and metric selection.
M|4. I|**Qu|** Are you identifying, discussing, and solving issues quickly?
M|4. I|**To|Issues Solving Track (IDS)**
M|4. I|tx|**I**dentify → **D**iscuss → **S**olve
M|4. I|**St|Identify**
M|4. I|it|What's the real issue? (Not the symptom)
M|4. I|it|Ask "Why?" until you reach root cause
M|4. I|it|State the issue in one sentence
M|4. I|**St|Discuss**
M|4. I|it|Everyone gets input (not equal time)
M|4. I|it|Tangents are stopped
M|4. I|it|Focus on the ONE issue
M|4. I|it|Time-boxed (usually 5-15 minutes)
M|4. I|**St|Solve**
M|4. I|it|Decision is made
M|4. I|it|Action items are assigned (who + what + when)
M|4. I|it|Move to nx issue
M|4. I|**Th|**
M|4. I|tx|\| tp \| Examples \| Action \|
M|4. I|tx|\|------\|----------\|--------\|
M|4. I|tx|\| **Problems** \| cs churn, team conflict, sy outage \| IDS → solve \|
M|4. I|tx|\| **Ideas** \| New feature, process change, mk opportunity \| IDS → decide (yes/no/later) \|
M|4. I|tx|\| **Obstacles** \| Blocking a rock, resource constraint, dependency \| IDS → remove or escalate \|
M|4. I|**Is|**
M|4. I|it|Everyone can add issues
M|4. I|- Pr|most important first
M|4. I|it|Not all issues get solved every meeting
M|4. I|it|Unsolved issues carry forward
M|4. I|**Co|**
M|4. I|it|Discussing symptoms, not root cause
M|4. I|it|Rehashing same issue every week
M|4. I|it|No clear action items
M|4. I|it|Too much discussion, not enough solving
M|4. I|See|[references/issues.md](references/issues.md) for IDS facilitation guides.
M|5. P|**Qu|** Have you documented and consistently followed your core processes?
M|5. P|**To|Core Process doc**
M|5. P|**Th|** Document 20% of your processes to get 80% consistency.
M|5. P|**Id|**
M|5. P|it|HR process (hiring, onboarding, reviews)
M|5. P|it|Sales process (lead → close)
M|5. P|it|Operations process (delivery, fulfillment)
M|5. P|it|cs service process (support → resolution)
M|5. P|it|fi process (invoicing, collections)
M|5. P|**Do|**
M|5. P|tx|1. Name the process
M|5. P|tx|2. List 5-20 major steps
M|5. P|tx|3. Add just enough detail (not a 50-page manual)
M|5. P|tx|4. Make it visual where possible
M|5. P|**Ex|Sales Process "The Closer"**
M|5. P|1. Q|Budget, Authority, Need, Timeline)
M|5. P|tx|2. Discovery call (30 min, use question guide)
M|5. P|tx|3. Demo (customize to their pain points)
M|5. P|tx|4. Proposal (send within 24 hours)
M|5. P|tx|5. Follow up (3 touches in 7 days)
M|5. P|tx|6. Close or disqualify
M|5. P|**Fo|**
M|5. P|it|Document it
M|5. P|it|Train on it
M|5. P|it|Measure compliance
M|5. P|it|up quarterly
M|5. P|See|[references/process.md](references/process.md) for process doc templates.
M|6. T|**Qu|** Are you executing on your vision every day?
M|6. T|**Tw|Rocks and Level 10 Meetings**
M|Rock|**De|** The 3-7 most important things to accomplish in the nx 90 days.
M|Rock|tx|**Why 90 days?**
M|Rock|it|Long enough to accomplish something meaningful
M|Rock|it|Short enough to maintain urgency
M|Rock|it|Natural human rhythm for focus
M|Rock|**Ro|**
M|Rock|tx|1. rv V/TO (vision, 3-year, 1-year)
M|Rock|2. B|"What must get done this quarter to stay on track?"
M|Rock|tx|3. Narrow to 3-7 company rocks
M|Rock|tx|4. Assign each rock to one owner
M|Rock|tx|5. Each leadership member also has 3-7 individual rocks
M|Rock|tx|6. Share w/ entire organization
M|Rock|tx|7. Track weekly
M|Rock|**SM|**
M|Rock|- **|"Launch new pricing page" not "improve pricing"
M|Rock|- **|Clear completion criteria
M|Rock|- **|Can be done in 90 days
M|Rock|- **|Given current resources
M|Rock|- **|Due end of quarter
M|Rock|**Ro|**
M|Rock|it|**Done** = checked off (no partial credit)
M|Rock|it|**Not done** = carried forward or dropped
M|Rock|- **|** 80%+ completion rate
M|Rock|**An|**
M|Rock|it|Too many rocks (>7) → Focus is diluted
M|Rock|it|Rocks too vague → Can't tell if done
M|Rock|it|No owner → Nobody accountable
M|Rock|it|All rocks are "business as usual" → Not moving the needle
M|Rock|See|[references/rocks.md](references/rocks.md) for rock-setting exercises.
M|Leve|tx|**The most important meeting in EOS.** Runs every week, same day, same time, same agenda.
M|Leve|**Du|** 90 minutes, never longer.
M|Leve|**Ag|**
M|Leve|tx|\| Time \| Section \| Purpose \|
M|Leve|tx|\|------\|---------\|---------\|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **Segue** \| Good news (personal and professional) \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **Scorecard** \| rv weekly numbers \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **Rock rv** \| On track / Off track for each rock \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **cs/Employee Headlines** \| Quick updates \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **To-Do List** \| rv last week's to-dos (done or not done) \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 60 min \| **IDS** \| Identify, Discuss, Solve issues \|
M|Leve|tx|\| 5 min \| **Conclude** \| Recap to-dos, rate meeting 1-10 \|
M|Leve|**Le|**
M|Leve|it|Starts on time, ends on time (non-negotiable)
M|Leve|it|Same day, same time every week
M|Leve|it|No phones/laptops (except for agenda)
M|Leve|it|IDS gets 60 of 90 minutes (most important part)
M|Leve|- Ra|8+)
M|Leve|it|If below 8, discuss what to improve
M|Leve|tx|**Why "Level 10"?**
M|Leve|it|Every meeting is rated 1-10 by participants
M|Leve|it|Goal is to consistently achieve 10/10
M|Leve|**To|**
M|Leve|it|7-day action items only
M|Leve|it|Each has owner and due date
M|Leve|it|Done = 100% complete
M|Leve|it|90%+ completion rate is target
M|Leve|See|[references/level-10.md](references/level-10.md) for meeting facilitation guides.
M|EOS |**Ty|2 years to full implementation**
M|EOS |tx|\| Phase \| Timeline \| Focus \|
M|EOS |tx|\|-------\|----------\|-------\|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Focus Day** \| Day 1 (8 hours) \| Accountability chart, rocks, scorecard, Level 10 \|
M|EOS || **|core values, core focus, 10-year target \|
M|EOS || **|mk st, 3-year, 1-year, rocks \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Quarterly sn** \| Every 90 days \| rv rocks, set new rocks, IDS major issues \|
M|EOS |tx|\| **Annual Planning** \| Yearly \| Full V/TO rv, set 1-year plan, Q1 rocks \|
M|EOS |**Se|**
M|EOS |- Se|Read the book, follow the tools (free, slower)
M|EOS |- EO|Certified facilitator guides the process (faster, expensive)
M|Orga|Rate|
M|Orga|tx|\| cp \| Statement \| Score (1-5) \|
M|Orga|tx|\|-----------\|-----------\|-------------\|
M|Orga|tx|\| **Vision** \| Leadership team is on the same page w/ where we're going and how to get there \| \|
M|Orga|tx|\| **People** \| We have the right people in the right seats \| \|
M|Orga|tx|\| **Data** \| We manage from a weekly scorecard of 5-15 numbers \| \|
M|Orga|tx|\| **Issues** \| We solve issues quickly and permanently \| \|
M|Orga|tx|\| **Process** \| Core processes are documented and followed by all \| \|
M|Orga|tx|\| **Traction** \| We set and achieve 90-day priorities (rocks) \| \|
M|Orga|**Sc|**
M|Orga|- 25|Strong (maintain and fine-tune)
M|Orga|- 20|Good (close gaps)
M|Orga|- 15|Average (sig work needed)
M|Orga|- Be|Weak (consider EOS implementer)
M|Comm|tx|\| Mistake \| Why It Fails \| Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|-------------\|------\|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Skipping Level 10s** \| Lose weekly rhythm, issues pile up \| Protect meeting, never cancel \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Too many rocks** \| No focus, nothing gets done \| Max 7 company rocks, 3-7 per person \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Vague rocks** \| Can't tell if done \| Write SMART rocks w/ clear criteria \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No scorecard** \| Managing by gut, surprises \| Choose 5-15 weekly numbers \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Wrong people kept** \| Drags entire team down \| Use People Analyzer, make tough calls \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **V/TO not shared** \| Team doesn't know the vision \| Share w/ entire company \|
M|Quic|Audi|
M|Quic|tx|\| Question \| If No \| Action \|
M|Quic|tx|\|----------\|-------\|--------\|
M|Quic|tx|\| Does leadership agree on vision? \| Misalignment \| Complete V/TO together \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Right people in right seats? \| perf issues \| People Analyzer on all seats \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Managing from data weekly? \| Reactive management \| bd weekly scorecard \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Issues solved permanently? \| Same problems repeat \| im IDS in Level 10s \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Core processes documented? \| Inconsistency \| Document top 5 processes \|
M|Quic|tx|\| 90-day priorities set and tracked? \| No traction \| Set quarterly rocks \|
